<paragraph blockId="1.[826,1442,1537,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[826,947,1537,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="208">Etymology:</emphasis>
Species name is derived from the Latin words ‘rectus’ (straight) and ‘unguis’ (claw), referring to the barely curved manual claws characterizing this taxon.
</paragraph>
